'''Bhalchandra Vaman Kelkar''' ({{lang-mr|भालचंद्र वामन केळकर}}) (September 23, 1920 – November 6, 1987) was a [[Marathi language|Marathi]] writer and actor, from [[Maharashtra]], [[India]].  He was one of the founders of Progressive Dramatic Association in [[Pune]].
<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2001-10-13/pune/27239714_1_pda-amateur-theatre-theatre-festival|title=Curtain goes up on a new act at PDA|date=October 13, 2001|publisher=Times Of India |accessdate=September 23, 2011}}</ref>

Bhalba Kelkar was also known for writing biographies of Indian scientists for children.

