{{Expand Turkish|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox writer | name = Cemâl Süreya | image = Cemal Sureya.jpg | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Cemalettin Seber | birth_date = 1931 | birth_place = [[Erzincan]], [[Turkey]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1990|1|9|1931}} | death_place = [[Istanbul]], Turkey | nationality = Turkish | occupation = Poet, writer | years_active = 1953–1990 | known_for = | alma_mater = [[Faculty of Political Science, Ankara University]] | spouse = {{plain list| * {{marriage | Seniha Seber| 1954 | 1962}} * {{marriage | Zühal Tekkanat| 1967 | 1975}} * {{marriage | Güngör Demiray| 1975 | 1975}} * {{marriage | Birsen Sağnak | 1980 | 1990}} }} | children = 2 | notable_works = }} {{History of Turkish literature}} '''Cemâl Süreya''' (born '''Cemâlettin Seber'''; 1931 – 9 January 1990) was a Turkish poet and writer of [[Zazas|Zaza]] descent.
==Biography== Of [[Alevi]] origin, after the 1938 [[Dersim Rebellion]], Süreya and his family were displaced to [[Bilecik]], a city in the [[Marmara Region]] of [[Turkey]].
He graduated from the Political Sciences Faculty of [[Ankara University]]. He was the editor-in-chief of the ''[[Papirüs]]'' [[literary magazine]]. Cemal Süreya is a notable member of the [[Turkish literature#Poetry|Second New Generation]] of [[Turkish poetry]], an abstract and postmodern movement created as a backlash against the more popular-based [[Garip]] movement. Love, mainly through its erotic character, is a popular theme of Süreya's works. Süreya's poems and articles were published in magazines such as ''Yeditepe'', ''Yazko'', ''Pazar Postası'', ''Yeni Ulus'', ''Oluşum'', ''Türkiye Yazıları'', ''Politika'', ''Aydınlık'', and ''Somut''. He is known to have been a primary influence on the poetry of [[Sunay Akın]].{{Citation needed|date=August 2011}} He lost a letter "y" from his pen name – originally Süreyya – because of a lost bet with Turkish poet [[Sezai Karakoç]].<ref name="Cemal Sureya">{{cite web|url=http://www.gastebursa.com/enCokOkunan/2011/11/12/29037/cemal-sureya-y-harfini-nasil-kaybetti.htm |title=Cemal Süreya 'y' harfini nasıl kaybetti? |publisher=Gastebursa.com |date=12 November 2011 |accessdate=2012-10-16 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130124195619/http://www.gastebursa.com/enCokOkunan/2011/11/12/29037/cemal-sureya-y-harfini-nasil-kaybetti.htm |archivedate=24 January 2013 |deadurl=yes |df=dmy }}</ref>
