'''Nyelâyu''' (Yâlayu), more commonly known as Nyelâyu, is a [[Kanak languages|Kanak language]] of northern [[New Caledonia]], spoken by approximately 2,000 speakers.   There are two dialects that are not mutually intelligible. Pooc (or Haat) is spoken in the Belep islands, which are located just north of [[Grande Terre (New Caledonia)|Grande Terre]]. Puma (or Paak or Ovac) is spoken in the northermost regions of New Caledonia in the areas around [[Poum]] in the west and [[Pouébo]] and [[Balade (New Caledonia)|Balade]] in the east.

