Voiceless stops, nasals, and approximants exhibit a constrast of aspiration exhibited in the following examples.

pe [pe] "ray fish" || phe [pʰe] "sharpening stone"

teec [teec] "scorching" || theec [tʰeec] "washed up"

nu [nu] "coconut palm" || nhu [nʰu] "hot"

Aspirated consonants are very subtly marked. Aspiration seems to be a prosodic trait that affects the overall realization of the syllable by lowering the register of the voice. <ref name="FOR">{{cite book |last1=Ozanne-Rivierre |first1=Françoise |title=Le Nyelâyu de Balade (Nouvelle-Calédonie) |date=1998 |publisher=Peeters Press |location=Paris}}</ref>

