{{distinguish|Omotic languages}} {{Infobox language |name=Omotik |nativename=Laamoot |states=Kenya |region=[[Great Rift Valley, Kenya]] |ethnicity=200 Omotiks (2000)<ref name=e18/> |speakers= 50 older adults |date=1980 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Eastern Sudanic languages|Eastern Sudanic]] |fam3=[[Kir–Abbaian languages|Kir–Abbaian]] |fam4=[[Nilotic languages|Nilotic]] |fam5=[[Southern Nilotic languages|Southern Nilotic]] |fam6=Omotik–Datooga |iso3=omt |glotto=omot1239 |glottorefname=Omotik }}
'''Omotik''' (Sawas) is a moribund [[Nilotic languages|Nilotic language]] of Kenya. It is spoken by the [[hunter-gatherer]] [[Omotik people]] of the [[Great Rift Valley, Kenya|Great Rift Valley]] among the [[Maasai people|Maasai]]; most of the Omotik population has shifted to the [[Maasai language]].
